<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.7111/52.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My February 21. Sir Edward Grey requests me to add the information that
                            the Governor of the Gold Coast Colony telegraphs to the effect that the
                            leases Sam is said to have acquired in the Colony have not been
                            registered here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>